abstract: An S.U.V. that offers a dizzying number of choices and the ability to handle more than many drivers will need.

lead_paragraph: IT can be argued that the Ford Explorer ignited America’s love affair with sport utility vehicles when it arrived in 1990, riding on the compact Ranger pickup platform.

abstract: A MacArthur fellow and the second-youngest woman ever elected to the National Academy of Sciences.
snippet: A MacArthur fellow and the second-youngest woman ever elected to the National Academy of Sciences.
lead_paragraph: Deborah S. Jin, a much-honored physicist who created and explored matter that exists only at a sliver of a degree above absolute zero — or minus 459.67 degrees Fahrenheit — died on Sept. 15 in Boulder, Colo. She was 47.

abstract: Mr. Adelson, the Las Vegas casino magnate, donated $40 million to Republicans in House and Senate races, with only $5 million going to Mr. Trump’s campaign.
snippet: Mr. Adelson, the Las Vegas casino magnate, donated $40 million to Republicans in House and Senate races, with only $5 million going to Mr. Trump’s campaign.
lead_paragraph: The Las Vegas billionaire Sheldon G. Adelson and his wife are giving more than $40 million to groups backing Republican congressional candidates, according to campaign filings and interviews with Republican strategists, disregarding repeated entreaties for support from allies of Donald J. Trump and dealing a major setback to Mr. Trump’s efforts to rally the deepest-pocketed Republican givers.

abstract: There are no longer great physical challenges in driving a Formula One car, but the sport remains largely a men's club.
snippet: There are no longer great physical challenges in driving a Formula One car, but the sport remains largely a men's club.
lead_paragraph: When Formula One returned from its summer break for the Belgian Grand Prix on Aug. 28, a series that used to separate the boys from the men suddenly found itself with two teenagers on the grid.

abstract: The carmaker, this time getting out in front of a safety problem, will recall 4.3 million vehicles worldwide to fix airbags that may not deploy in a crash.
snippet: The carmaker, this time getting out in front of a safety problem, will recall 4.3 million vehicles worldwide to fix airbags that may not deploy in a crash.
lead_paragraph: Concerns about automobile airbags lately have focused on ones that deploy too explosively or even spontaneously.
